  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>FastAPI Backend</strong>: Async/await, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Alembic
      migrations.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Next.js 16 Frontend</strong>: App Router, Tailwind CSS,
      TypeScript.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>RAG Pipeline</strong>: Document chunking, embeddings, vector
      search, and reranking.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>4 LLM Providers</strong>: OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Ollama.
    </li>
    <li><strong>3 Vector Databases</strong>: Qdrant, Weaviate, pgvector.</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Dual Auth</strong>: Clerk (primary) + JWT (service-to-service).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Example</h2>
  <pre
    class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto border border-slate-800"><code class="text-slate-300"># Create project
npx create-ai-stack@latest my-ai-app

# Start infrastructure
cd my-ai-app
docker-compose up -d

# Run migrations
cd apps/backend && uv run alembic upgrade head

# Start development
uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload</code></pre>

  <h2>Philosophy</h2>
  <p>
    We follow the <strong>ai-stack</strong> philosophy: opinionated but modular, typesafe,
    and production-ready from day one. You shouldn't have to rewrite your entire stack
    just to switch from OpenAI to Anthropic, or from Qdrant to pgvector.
  </p>

